      "summary": "The cryptocurrency market experienced a surge following the House's passing of President Donald Trump's $3.3 trillion domestic agenda package just before the July 4 holiday. At 11.26 p.m. ET, Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) rose by 0.47% to $109,230, Ethereum (CRYPTO: ETH) increased by 0.51% to $2,579, and Dogecoin (CRYPTO: DOGE) fell by 1.12% to $0.1708. The total crypto market capitalization reached $3.37 trillion, growing by 0.42% in 24 hours, with Bitcoin holding 64.5% dominance and Ethereum at 9.2% market share. The market's volatility continued, resulting in 87,335 traders being liquidated in the past day, amounting to $217.42 million. Open Interest in crypto derivatives rose to $151.69 billion, up 0.95%, while the U.S. Dollar Index decreased by 0.14%. This surge followed House Republicans' approval of Trump's comprehensive legislative package, including tax cuts, military and border security funding, and reductions in federal safety nets. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.",
      "source_type": "news",
      "headline": "Cryptocurrency market surges as Trump passes $3.3 trillion bill. Bitcoin at $109,230, Ethereum at $2,579, Dogecoin at $0.1708. Market cap at $3.37 trillion. 87,335 traders liquidated in 24 hours. Bitcoin maintains 64.5% dominance. Open Interest in crypto derivatives at $151.69 billion. U.S. Dollar Index down 0.14%.",
